  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "gPbB4oP4esvnqpDRy+qIewGaQKs=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:30.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# createSwarmSyncBuilder Integration Hook\n\nThe adapter exposes `createSwarmSyncBuilder()` from `src/channel/create-composite-factory.ts` as the single sanctioned entry point for integrating Swarm sync into a Reactor host via the official `ReactorBuilder` API.\n\nThis replaces an earlier monkey-patching approach. The builder installs a `CompositeChannelFactory` that routes sync channels by their `config.type` discriminator:\n\n- `\"gql\"` \u2192 `GqlRequestChannel` (Switchboard cloud sync)\n- `\"swarm\"` \u2192 `SwarmChannel` (Swarm decentralized sync)\n\nThis lets a single Reactor instance run GraphQL-based Switchboard sync and Swarm-based decentralized sync side-by-side, per-drive, without either sync path interfering with the other. Per-drive registration happens through `add-swarm-remote.ts`.\n\nThe builder pattern is the stable public surface for adapter consumers \u2014 downstream apps should wire Swarm sync via `createSwarmSyncBuilder()` rather than constructing `SwarmChannel` directly.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:30.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:30.000Z"
    }
  },
